<TEXT>
n Cairn Energy has begun drilling the first offshore gas exploration well to be
sunk in Bangladesh for more than 20 years. The Edinburgh-based oil company
yesterday began work on the Sangu-1 well in offshore block 16, 35km south-west
of the port city of Chittagong. Cairn hopes it will prove gas reserves of more
than 1.5 trillion cubic feet.
It expects to take about 40 days to drill the 3500m well which marks the start
of a three-year exploration and appraisal campaign by Cairn in offshore blocks
15 and 16.
