<DATE>951206</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Player in the clear</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>KEN SMITH</BYLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>1</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975028239</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
ABERDEEN Football Club captain Stewart McKimmie will not be prosecuted for an
elbowing incident which led to him being sent off in the match against Partick
Thistle in Glasgow on Saturday.
Procurator-fiscal Andrew Normand, who originally called for a police report,
has said he is taking no further action.
McKimmie has already been fined #500 by his club.
The growing involvement of fiscals' departments in on-the-field violence has
led to calls from some football and legal officials for fresh guidelines.
q A bid by Everton striker Duncan Ferguson for an immediate return to football
is expected to start today at the Court of Session, but a full hearing will not
take place for some time.
</TEXT>
