<DATE>951206</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Woman killed in A1 pile-up</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>5</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975028258</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A WOMAN died and six others were seriously injured in a multiple smash near
roadworks on the A1 last night.
Fire teams, a medical flying squad from Edinburgh Royal Infirmary, and
paramedics went to the scene between Haddington and Gladsmuir, East Lothian.
Three cars and an articulated lorry are understood to have been involved.
Fire teams had to use cutting equipment to free victims and the road was closed
and diversions set up.
The accident happened close to a section of the A1 which is restricted in width
for resurfacing.
</TEXT>
