<DOCNO>GH951206-000037</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH951206-000037</DOCID>
<DATE>951206</DATE>
<HEADLINE>`Music' could strike the right note</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>27</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975028263</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
KIM Bailey, who has virtually discounted Master Oats from the King George VI
Chase on Boxing Day, could still be represented in the race by Book of Music.
As the trainer awaits an explanation for the Gold Cup winner's recent flop at
Chepstow, he is planning a Christmas comeback for one of the most impressive
winners of last season.
Book of Music easily beat Martin's Lamp on his only start last season and,
having recovered from injury, is on the Gold Cup trail as well as Master Oats.
He is entered in Kempton's highlight, for which he is priced 16-1.
``Book of Music will run somewhere over the Christmas period,'' said Bailey,
``but I have not made my mind up where yet. He might go for the King George if
the field cut up but it is only a slight chance at the moment.
``I am not keen to run him in handicaps because he is high in the weights.''
</TEXT>
