<HEADLINE>BUT DO YOU REALLY NEED THE BUTLER'S PANTRY?</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>1</PAGE>
<FLAG>Scotlands Homes</FLAG>
<GRAPHIC>Photograph</GRAPHIC>
<RECORDNO>975028265</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THE impressive range of large villas in Helensburgh - surprising for a small
town - developed during the last century as Glasgow's merchants and bankers
used the railway to escape from the fumes of the city each evening.
Times may have changed, but Helensburgh's qualities are timeless and its large
houses are still very much sought after.
Slater Hogg &amp; Howison is currently marketing one charming example next to the
golf course on Golfhill Drive. Hillcrest is a detached period villa standing in
well-stocked gardens which extend to half an acre.
The accommodation consists of vestibule, inner hallway with an oak parquet
flooring, a lounge with a French door which leads to the terrace, sitting room,
formal dining room, fitted kitchen with white goods, breakfast room, utility
room - and butler's pantry - and five bedrooms upstairs.
The main bedroom has an en-suite bathroom and access to a balcony. The property
comes with a double garage and out-houses. Offers over #205,000 are invited.
</TEXT>
