<HEADLINE>HIE has promotion taped</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>19</PAGE>
<GRAPHIC>Photograph</GRAPHIC>
<RECORDNO>975028297</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
HIGHLANDS and Islands Enterprise has found a novel method of driving home the
message about the North of Scotland's advantages as a location for business and
industry.
Some 5000 cassette tapes are being distributed to drivers hiring cars from
Hertz at Glasgow, Edinburgh, and Inverness airports over the next three months.
The tapes carry a 30-minute programme about the area and include interviews
with businessmen and women, interspersed with music from artists such as
Capercaillie and Orkney composer Peter Maxwell Davis. The package includes a
reply-paid card for additional information.
Firms from across the HIE area are featured, including Judane Knitwear from
Shetland, Caithness freezer firm Norfrost and Loch Fyne Oysters from Argyll.
HIE's senior marketing manager, Stewart Miller, said: ``Inward investment is
increasingly competitive and it is vital to bring your message to the direct
attention of potential developers.''
</TEXT>
