<DATE>951206</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Cadets made to eat cigarettes</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>3</EDITION>
<PAGE>8</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975028331</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THREE police academy instructors lost their jobs after ordering two cadets to
eat cigarette sandwiches as punishment for smoking.
The cadets vomited. One collapsed and was taken unconscious to a hospital.
``There were three training advisers involved in the incident. As of today they
are no longer employed,'' said Hugh Foster, director of the Criminal Justice
Training Centre at Golden West College, Huntington Beach, California.
The two cadets admitted being smokers during an inspection on Friday and were
then ordered to eat cigarette sandwiches. They have recovered, Foster said.
``The recruits were ordered to place their cigarettes between two pieces of
bread and to take two bites each,'' said Foster. ``After that, they were given
about 250 push-ups and 50 pull-ups.''
Both cadets remain in the training programme and are expected to be among 22
classmates graduating on Friday.-AP.
</TEXT>
