<DOCID>GH951206-000106</DOCID>
<DATE>951206</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Catholics fight ban</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>7</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975028332</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
TWO hundred Roman Catholic members of St Paul's parish in Edinburgh's Muirhouse
have objected to the Vatican over the suppression of an educational pack
intended to teach school pupils about the dangers of HIV and Aids.
The parishioners said in a petition that the pack had been produced to enable
teachers and youth workers to provide young people with the knowledge needed to
avoid the risk of the HIV virus.
The parishioners said the pack had been effectively banned without any
consultation.
</TEXT>
