<HEADLINE>Smith books  #8m contract</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>21</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975028334</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
SCOTTISH bookseller John Smith &amp; Son has won an #8m contract to supply books
and CD-ROMs to British Council libraries throughout the world.
The Glasgow-based chain of 10 bookshops is setting up a special department to
handle the three-year contract to provide 185 British Council libraries in 108
countries.
Managing director Willie Anderson said: ``We have worked closely with the
council for over 20 years now on different projects and we are extremely
pleased to be co-operating with them in what must be one of the premier library
contracts in the UK.''
</TEXT>
