<HEADLINE>Siebe on target as sales soar</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>19</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975028494</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
THE ever confident Barrie Stephens repeated yesterday that engineering giant
Siebe had continued on target after half-year pre-tax profits jumped 20.6% to
#144m on a sales gain of 18.6% to #1200m.
He added that the two control divisions achieved record levels of sales and
operating profits, and the investment and restructuring at diversified products
was delivering increased sales and profits. The order book stands at a record
#770m.
Siebe, which is Britain's biggest diversified engineering group incorporating
more than 125 companies across the world, is increasing the interim dividend
10% to 4.44p.
The group's American businesses were affected by a reduced house-building
programme and a cut-back in vehicle production. Siebe shares jumped 29p to 768p.
